parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and corrosion of the frame can cause structural damage, leading to a loss of vehicle integrity, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rusting and corrosion of the frame
holes in the frame
bowing of the frame
detachment of the fuel tank
and failure of the exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint defects and body rot can lead to corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Paint chipping and peeling
rusting of the body
and corrosion of the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frame rust and corrosion can lead to structural failure, affecting vehicle safety and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Holes in the frame
rusted-through frame
excessive corrosion on suspension components
and rust flaking off cross members and welds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear leaf spring failure can cause the vehicle to sag, affecting handling and stability, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Broken rear leaf spring
excessive rust on leaf springs
and abnormal noise from the suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or incomplete recall repairs can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, posing a risk to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: Dealerships refusing to perform recall repairs
parts not available
and manufacturers not providing assistance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often while braking or shifting gears. The accelerator pedal may stick or become lodged under the floor mat
and the brakes may not respond properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The floor mat can interfere with the accelerator pedal, causing unintended acceleration and loss of control.
symptoms: The floor mat becomes stuck under the accelerator pedal
preventing the pedal from returning to its normal position. The driver may experience difficulty braking or shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electronic throttle control system can malfunction, causing unintended acceleration and loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without any apparent reason. The accelerator pedal may not respond properly
and the brakes may not be effective.
